				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fantasy Books with Bards (Recommendations, please)<a name="29509"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 22 04 6:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;The Riddle Master if Hed&quot;, first book in a three book set by Patricia A. McKillip (sp). The second is called  &quot;Heir of Sea and Fire&quot;, the third is called &quot;Harpest in the Wind&quot;. Thee of my favorits by one of my favorit authors. They are old, so you may not find them at the local Boarders, but you can always get them on amazon.com. There is a new edition, all three in a single volume if you don't want them seperat.
<br />

<br />
There is in fact not a lot of music in them (though there is a really cool harp), most of the secreat clues and information is in the form of riddles. Still they are very cool, IMO.
<br />

<br />
One of her books that is very concerned with music is calle &quot;A Song for the Basalisk&quot;. It's a newer book, and her writing has become more sophisticated since &quot;Riddle Master&quot; (not a suprize, the &quot;Riddle Master&quot; books must be 30 years old) so those of you who may not have liked her earler work might want to give her another chance.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
