				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fantasy Books with Bards (Recommendations, please)<a name="29595"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 23 04 6:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You want to see a series in which bards are the be-all-and-end all?  I recommend the Quartered Series by Tanya Huff.
<br />
Sing the Four Quarters is the first in the series, and the best to start with as it sets up the backdrop for the rest of the series.
<br />
Here, bards are THE thing.  There aren't any wizards or anything, bards are the only one with any kind of &quot;magical&quot; powers.  Aside from that, its still a really cool series with an excellent take on how magic works in a world.  I recommend this series for anyone, but I HIGHLY recommend it for anyone who loves bards and wants to see them get the R-E-S-P-E-C-T they deserve <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />
Edit: Here's the amazon site for it: <a target="_new" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0886776287/qid=1080039894/sr=8-1/ref=sr_8_xs_ap_i1_xgl14/104-9440877-7150304?v=glance&amp;s=books&amp;n=507846">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0886776287/qid=1080039894/sr=8-1/ref=sr_8_xs_ap_i1_xgl14/104-9440877-7150304?v=glance&amp;s=books&amp;n=507846</a>
<br />
Myrmion
<br />
65 Bard, Xegony</span></td>
