				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fantasy Books with Bards (Recommendations, please)<a name="29924"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 23 04 4:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Evangeline Walton wrote a book called The Mabinogion, closely based on a medieval book of Welsh legends of the same name.  
<br />

<br />
It is interesting not only as a motherlode of fantasy themes but the Bard appears as an important figure.   Given that the original Mabinogion is probably 800 years old or more, this has to be one of the earliest bard references there is.  
<br />

<br />
Not to mention it's a bloody good read =)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
